	// Acquire a file-based lock to prevent concurrent refresh
	lockPath, err := reauthLockPath()
	if err != nil {
		return nil, err
	}
	unlock, err := acquireReauthLock(lockPath)
	if err != nil {
		return nil, fmt.Errorf("another reauth in progress: %w", err)
	}
	defer unlock()

	// Re-read auth after acquiring lock - another process may have refreshed
	af, err = LoadAuth()  // Line 67 - double-check AFTER lock
```

**Double-check after lock acquisition:** YES - Line 67 re-reads auth after acquiring the lock.

**Claims: TRUE (TOCTOU race exists) and TRUE (double-check exists)**

